title: 10 reasons to visit Tuolomne County now
text:
Photo: James Tensuan Freshly picked apples are seen at Indigeny in Sonora. The 160-acre distillery features tastings, tours and picnic areas. Freshly picked apples are seen at Indigeny in Sonora. The 160-acre...
From fresh apple pies and free-range turkey to cut-your-own Christmas trees and Halloween train rides, Tuolumne County provides plenty of options for celebrating fall and winter holidays. Plus, sunny autumn days with cool, clear nights are perfect for exploring the greater Yosemite area, minus the summer crowds.
